KAITO: Hehe. Sounds like Emu and the others are all here...
KAITO: Ready, everyone?
Rin & Len: Ready!
Luka: This is to put smiles on all their faces.
Miku: Let's do our best, you guys!!!
Rin & Co.: Yeah! Yes! Let's!
MEIKO: Once upon a time, there was an eccentric traveling theater troupe♪
Nene: Oh, MEIKO's narrating...
MEIKO: The troupe consists of a show-offy troupe leader...
MEIKO: A clown who won't listen...
MEIKO: And a songstress who can't sing in public!
Rui: I see. They've swapped roles since last time...
MEIKO: The oddball group staged many shows, but they never managed to attract an audience!
MEIKO: Then one day, as they were traveling through a forest, they encountered an alchemist who was performing a show all alone.
Emu: (Hehe. The troupe's all here...!)
Emu: (I can't wait to see how they're gonna do this!)
Troupe Leader: “I am a showman, and I could use your help to put on wonderful shows!”
Troupe Leader: “I promise that our spectacles will be a joy to see and a joy to perform in!”
Alchemist: “You wish to make shows with me? I see. I suppose I could help you out a little.”
Clown: “Yaaay! Welcome to our troupe!”
Songstress: “But will I...find the courage to sing?”
Fairy: “Why were you making shows? Wasn't it because you wanted to make people happy?”
MEIKO: The showman remembered the first time he saw a theatrical performance, and regretted the way he treated his troupe members.
Troupe Leader: “I've always wanted to become a star like the actors in the first show I saw. I wanted to be a star so that I too could make people as happy as I was then.”
Troupe Leader: “It was very important to me, but I forgot it along the way. I shall never forget it again!”
Troupe Leader: “What I want is to make people smile. I want to perform with my troupe again!”
Nene: Hehe. This really takes me back.
Rui: Yes. It's as if this all happened just yesterday.
Emu: ...
Emu: (It's about to end...)
Emu: (With, “And they made shows together forever after”...)
Emu: ...
MEIKO: They continued merrily making shows together.
MEIKO: But one day, they each began to dream of different things.
Emu: What...?
MEIKO: The troupe leader wished to become an even bigger star.
MEIKO: The songstress wished to sing all around the world.
MEIKO: The alchemist wished to put on a show that would make anybody and everybody smile.
Emu: (They changed the ending...?)
MEIKO: And the clown...
MEIKO: ...wished to fill the village where she met her dear friends with smiles and happiness.
Emu: ...!
Emu: (Hang on...)
Emu: (Is this about us...?)
MEIKO: Each of these dreams was very meaningful to them. Thus, they decided to go their separate ways.
MEIKO: But they also made a promise together.
Troupe Leader: “One day... One day, when we've all achieved our dreams...”
Troupe Leader: “Let's meet again here. To put on another show!”
Clown: “Yeah...!!!”
MEIKO: And so, time went on...
MEIKO: It was only a blink of an eye compared to the span of a person's life. But it must've felt like an eternity to these four...
MEIKO: Fortunately, by the time the clown had built an amusement park that made everybody in the village smile and laugh...
MEIKO: They all returned.
Troupe Leader: “Hey, we're back!”
Clown: “What?! Oh, does this mean...?!”
Troupe Leader: “Hm? Why the look of surprise?! I became a world-famous star just like I said I would! You should be happier!”
Songstress: “I made my dream come true as well! My singing can reach people all over the world!”
Alchemist: “Hehe. We apologize for appearing so suddenly. Anyway, let's get down to business...”
Alchemist: “What kind of show shall we put on?”
Clown: “Hehe...!”
Clown: “There's lots and lots of shows that I wanna do with you guys!”
Clown: “So, let's do them all...!”
MEIKO: Our four heroes continued following their various paths in life, but reunited as a troupe that would gather once again at the clown's amusement park from time to time...
MEIKO: And they made shows together forever after...
